Cyber Security</H2></center>
<br><br>
<p class="indent">About 2 years ago, a friend of mine gifted me with a lock pick set.  I thought to myself, "I've seen this done in the movies, but there is no way it is as easy as they make it out to be."  Within a couple hours, he and I were timing ourselves on 8 different locks, that we owned, to see who could pick them the fastest.  I learned an important lesson that day about physical security.  Locks only keep honest people honest.  Picking a lock does take a certain amount of skill, but once that is mastered, most locks are fairly easy to pick!</p>
<p class="indent">The same is true when it comes to cyber security... to a point.  A friend of mine from church, <a href="https://github.com/michael-david-fry">Michael</a> told me that he was attending a meetup once a week to learn about cyber security.  I saw this as an opportunity to tighten the security of the software I was developing.</p>
<p class="indent">Our first step was to install a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virtual_machine">Virtual Machine.</a>  We used <a href="https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Downloads">VirtualBox.</a>  Then we pulled down <a href="https://www.kali.org/">Kali.</a>  Kali is a Debian-derived Linux distribution designed for digital forensics and penetration testing.  Think of it like the lock pick set.  It is a set of tools you use to open doors.  From there, we went to <a href="http://overthewire.org/wargames/bandit/">Over the Wire</a> and began Bandit.  Bandit and othe games offered by the OverTheWire community can help you to learn and practice security concepts in the form of fun-filled games.</p>
<p class="indent">As of this moment, I am only at level 4 in Bandit, but I am learning how Hackers do what they do, Linux command line interaction, and how to guard against hackers.  After my enlightenment on the facade of physical locks, I went out and purchased locks that guard against being picked.  I expect that once I understand how to guard against hackers, you will see much more secure software developed whilst Coding in Clendinen.</p></div>
